300 2224 228 (Description:) 228 SB
600 2273 1459 (In the HP STL implementation, before allocator, collections did their own bulk) 1459 SB
600 2322 1408 (storage management.  Now that we have allocator objects that can be tuned) 1408 SB
600 2371 1421 (\(and, if necessary, specialized\) for the purpose, this function is not so useful,) 1421 SB
600 2420 793 (and indeed encourages a harmful practice.) 793 SB
600 2518 1455 (This member was omitted from the latest Draft, but not \(to my knowledge\) by) 1455 SB
600 2567 914 (any enabling motion.  We should make it official.) 914 SB
300 2616 213 (Discussion:) 213 SB
600 2665 1443 (Encouraging collections to perform bulk storage management is incompatible) 1443 SB
600 2714 1499 (with best performance in object databases.  Furthermore, such code obscures the) 1499 SB
600 2763 1388 (logic of containers, and tends to be identical or nearly so in each container,) 1388 SB
600 2812 1345 (resulting in wasteful duplication.  Such code was intended to reduce the) 1345 SB
600 2861 1472 (number of calls to the \(expensive\) global operator new\(\), but such optimization) 1472 SB
600 2910 804 (would better be performed in the allocator.) 804 SB
